========================================
*Pixes Kernel*
========================================

*Version:* 0.1-alpha
*Author:* Scripe3
*Website:* Scripe3.github.io/pixes-kernel(not active)

Pixes is a lightweight, open-source kernel designed for modern systems. 
It aims to provide a simple, efficient, and modular architecture for hobbyists 
and developers who want to build their own operating systems.

*Features:*
- Modular kernel architecture
- Basic memory management
- Simple task scheduler
- Support for multiple CPU cores (SMP)
- Basic driver framework

*Getting Started:*
1. Clone or download the Pixes source.
2. Follow the build instructions in BUILD.txt.
3. Compile using the recommended toolchain.
4. Run on QEMU or your target hardware.

*Contributing:*
Pixes welcomes contributions. Please follow the coding style
and guidelines provided in CONTRIBUTING.txt.

*Support:*
For questions and discussions, reach out via GitHub Issues or
your preferred open-source community platform.
